==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Generalization
<hw>Gen`er*al*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>g⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧ralisation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of generalizing; the act of
bringing individuals or particulars under a genus or class; deduction of
a general principle from particulars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Generalization</qex> is only the apprehension of the one in
the many.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A general inference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>generalize</ent>⟦br⟧
